---
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';

const clientNeeds = [
  'The date this statement is first published (your launch date).',
  'A dedicated email address for accessibility questions (we recommend accessibility@wellpeps.com — you decide if it should forward to an inbox you already check).',
  'A mailing address where formal written accessibility requests should go.',
  'How quickly you commit to acknowledging feedback (e.g. 3 business days) and proposing a fix or workaround (e.g. 10 business days).',
  'Who a complaint escalates to internally if the person is not satisfied — a name or a title (e.g. "Head of Operations").',
  'Confirmation that a customer really can do everything by phone — sign up, order, and manage their account — since the statement promises that as the accessible alternative.',
];
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement"
  description="WellPeps' commitment to digital accessibility and how to reach us if you encounter a barrier."
  clientNeeds={clientNeeds}
>
  <div class="callout callout--note">
    <strong>Before this page can go live</strong>
    <p>
      An accessibility statement is a promise, so it has to be backed by a check of the
      site. The WellPeps web team will run that check (an accessibility audit) and fill in
      the technical parts below. The blue items are theirs — not something you need to answer.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p class="legal__meta">
    Statement Date: <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: the date this goes live</span><br />
    Last Reviewed: <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: same as the date above for the first version</span>
  </p>

  <h2>1. Our Commitment</h2>
  <p>
    WellPeps is committed to making our website and services accessible to everyone, including
    people with disabilities. We believe access to telehealth information and care should not depend
    on ability, and we work to provide an experience that is perceivable, operable, understandable,
    and robust for all visitors.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Conformance Status</h2>
  <p>
    The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) are the recognized standard for making websites
    usable by people with disabilities. Sites are measured against three levels: A, AA, and AAA.
  </p>
  <p>
    <span class="ph ph--web">Web team: pick the correct sentence below after the audit — never publish the stronger claim without evidence to back it.</span>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Option A</strong> (only if a completed audit supports it): &ldquo;This website is
      fully conformant with WCAG 2.1 Level AA.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Option B</strong> (the honest default for most sites at launch): &ldquo;This website
      is partially conformant with WCAG 2.1 Level AA, meaning some parts of the content do not yet
      fully conform. We are actively working to achieve full conformance.&rdquo;
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Measures We Take</h2>
  <p>
    WellPeps takes the following measures to support accessibility.
    <span class="ph ph--web">Web team: keep only the lines that are actually true — each one is a factual claim the company is making.</span>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Include accessibility in our design and development standards for all new pages;</li>
    <li>
      Test with automated tools and manual keyboard and screen-reader review.
      <span class="ph ph--web">Web team: name the tools and screen readers actually used (e.g. axe, Lighthouse; NVDA, VoiceOver).</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      Maintain semantic HTML, sufficient color contrast, visible focus states, and support for
      reduced-motion preferences;
    </li>
    <li>
      Train our design and engineering team on accessible development practices.
      <span class="ph ph--web">Web team: confirm this is true, or remove the line.</span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Compatibility</h2>
  <p>
    This website is designed to be compatible with recent versions of major browsers (Chrome,
    Firefox, Safari, Edge) and with common assistive technologies, including screen readers and
    screen-magnification software, on desktop and mobile.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Known Limitations</h2>
  <p>
    Despite our efforts, some content may not yet be fully accessible.
    <span class="ph ph--web">Web team: list any known issues found in the audit, each with a target fix date. If the audit finds none, write &ldquo;No known limitations at this time.&rdquo;</span>
  </p>

  <h2>6. Alternative Access</h2>
  <p>
    If any part of this website is difficult to use, you can complete every step of the WellPeps
    process — including consultations, ordering, and account changes — by phone with our support
    team at <a href="tel:+18339357377">(833) 935-7377</a> (Mon–Fri, 9am–6pm ET).
    <span class="ph ph--you">You confirm: that phone support really can handle the whole journey, from signup to refill. If any step is web-only, tell us and we'll soften this sentence.</span>
  </p>

  <h2>7. Feedback and Contact</h2>
  <p>
    We welcome feedback on the accessibility of this website. If you encounter an accessibility
    barrier, please contact us:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: a monitored accessibility email address</span></li>
    <li>Phone: <a href="tel:+18339357377">(833) 935-7377</a></li>
    <li>Mail: <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: a mailing address for written requests</span></li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: e.g. 3 business days</span> and to propose a resolution or
    accessible alternative within <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: e.g. 10 business days</span>.
    This statement is reviewed and updated
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: how often — yearly at minimum, and after any major redesign</span>.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Enforcement and Formal Complaints</h2>
  <p>
    If you are not satisfied with our response, you may escalate your concern to
    <span class="ph ph--you">You provide: who this goes to internally — a name or job title</span>. U.S. users may also contact
    the U.S. Department of Justice regarding ADA concerns.
    <span class="ph ph--legal">Lawyer: confirm whether to keep the Department of Justice reference — included here as the transparent default.</span>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
